			<h2>
				Input Package
			</h2>
			<p>
				This is the root package name of your java project.
			</p>
			
			<div>
				Example:
			</div>
			<div>
				com.my.first.crm
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-4">
			<h2>
				Input Entity Name
			</h2>
			<p>
				This is name of the business entity you wish to generate all of the plumbing code for.
			</p>
			
			<div>
				Example:
			</div>
			<div>
				Customer
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-4">
			<h2>
				Click Generate
			</h2>
			<p>
				Once you click generate code you can visit the other tabs and download the code.
			</p>
			
			<div>
				Protip:
			</div>
			<div>
				Copy the code and simply paste it into the root package of your project. Eclipse will create the class and move it into the right package.
